<TITLE> BD Foods units gutted in Ctg </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Jan 15 (bdnews24.com)-- A fire burned down a fish-processing plant and cold storage of BD Foods Ltd at Sagarika Road in Chittagong on Thursday night. A company official claimed that the fire caused a loss of about Tk 1 billion as it gutted equipment and goods, but fire service put the figures at around Tk 10 million. Agrabad fire service mobilising officer Paban Kumar Talukder told bdnews24.com that the fire had originated from an electricity fault at around 10pm. On information, 12 fire-fighting vehicles rushed to the spot and managed to douse the blaze at around 2:45am. Talukder said four persons sustained minor injuries during the fire-fighting operation. BD Foods law officer Mamunur Rashid said the blaze damaged a specialised fish-processing plant of the company's factory and around 350 tonnes of frozen fish stored there. b
